From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <ge-proton@example.com>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 16:15:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] winepulse: Refresh DualSense mono only after hotplug.

Spider-Man Remastered opens a dedicated one-channel DualSense controller
speaker endpoint for small effect audio.  A normal startup with the
controller already present should not touch that Pulse stream when the
first non-silent effect burst arrives.

Keep the first-effect refresh for the cases it was added for, where a
controller was unplugged/replugged or swapped and the existing audio
client needs to recover.  If the stream is already ready and the hotplug
generation has not changed, simply mark the mono stream active and leave
the endpoint alone.
---
 dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c | 14 ++++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
index 22222222222..33333333333 100644
--- a/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
+++ b/dlls/winepulse.drv/pulse.c
@@ -3810,9 +3810,19 @@ static NTSTATUS pulse_release_render_buffer(void *args)
             stream->dualsense_mono_audio_active = FALSE;
         else if (!stream->dualsense_mono_audio_active)
         {
-            TRACE("Refreshing DualSense mono speaker stream before non-silent effect burst.\n");
+            unsigned int generation;
+
             stream->dualsense_mono_audio_active = TRUE;
-            pulse_dualsense_mono_reconnect_internal(stream, TRUE);
+
+            g_phys_lock();
+            generation = g_haptic_hotplug_generation;
+            g_phys_unlock();
+
+            if (!pulse_stream_ready(stream) || stream->haptic_hotplug_generation != generation)
+            {
+                TRACE("Refreshing DualSense mono speaker stream before non-silent effect burst.\n");
+                pulse_dualsense_mono_reconnect_internal(stream, TRUE);
+            }
         }
     }
 
